BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Somewhat True Tale of Robin Hood
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260719T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260719T153000
DTSTAMP:20260720T153526Z
UID:occ-608@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Mary Lynn Dobson's Monty Python-flavored Robin Hood spoof\, wi
 th spoon-wielding Merry Men and dessert at intermission.\n\nMary Lynn Dobs
 on's parody sends up the Robin Hood legend in full Monty Python spirit: a 
 preening hero in green\, a damsel fixated on her skin conditions\, a sheri
 ff who would rather be bowling\, and a band of Merry Men armed with spoons
  and a collective IQ of six. A cheerful "Town's Guy" keeps wandering into 
 scenes he has no business in. Walker Scott directs for Lionheart Theatre\,
  the Norcross community company\, and every ticket includes dessert at int
 ermission. Runs through July 19.
GEO:33.9421741;-84.2112431
LAST-MODIFIED:20260719T153558Z
LOCATION:Lionheart Theatre\, 10 College St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/35819/production/1270020/performance/1178630
 3
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Philadelphia Story
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260911T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260911T220000
DTSTAMP:20260720T153526Z
UID:occ-593@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Philip Barry's 1939 high-society comedy: a socialite's second 
 wedding\, crashed by her ex-husband and two tabloid journalists.\n\nPhilip
  Barry's 1939 comedy of the privileged class. Tracy Lord\, headstrong daug
 hter of the Philadelphia Lords\, is set to marry a successful young snob w
 hen her ex-husband and a pair of tabloid journalists descend on the family
  estate for the wedding weekend. Barry wrote the role for Katharine Hepbur
 n\, who backed the play with her own money and carried it into the 1940 fi
 lm with Cary Grant and James Stewart. Darci Rose Wells directs for Lionhea
 rt Theatre\, where every ticket includes dessert at intermission\; runs th
 rough September 27.
GEO:33.9421741;-84.2112431
LAST-MODIFIED:20260720T153514Z
LOCATION:Lionheart Theatre\, 10 College St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/35819/production/1276719/performance/1181317
 9
END:VEVENT
